{

If you lead the two high cards against a notrump contract and then lead the
suit again, you have established two winners. Note, however, that there may be
no entry to them if partner next gets the lead. Since declarer is entitled to
one trick, leading a low card costs nothing and avoids stranding your winners.

Against a suit contract, however, leading a low card would give declarer an
undeserved trick. Declarer may even be able to discard some losers and you may
not get either your ace or your king. By leading the ace, the king and then
another one, partner will be able to ruff.}
