{

You would lead the top of your interior sequence, the jack, against a notrump
contract. Declarer can win the queen, but if partner gets in to lead the suit
back, you end up taking four tricks since declarer’s king is trapped.

Against a suit contract, however, you may never get a trick with your ace if
you lead the jack. Declarer will win the first trick with the queen and may be
able to ruff the remaining two cards in the dummy. If you lead the suit, the
ace is safer, although you probably would be better off selecting a different
suit to lead.}
